The paper discusses distributed systems and data replication, which are typically studied in the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of Conflict-free Replicated Data Types (CRDTs) also suggests the Database (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also mentions reliable causal delivery, which is a topic in the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the use of Tagged Causal Stable Broadcast (TCSB) suggests the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category.
